h a cometary tail of dusty\neffluent material. The star hosts a dusty debris disk and the star's spectrum\nshows prominent lines from heavy elements like magnesium, aluminium, silicon,\ncalcium, iron, and nickel. This system provides evidence that heavy element\npollution of white dwarfs can originate from disrupted rocky bodies such as\nasteroids and minor planets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Oct 2015 19:45:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-10-22"}
